cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.DC

This paper is primarily focused on security and protection against side-channel attacks in Intel's SGX. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a compiler-based tool for implementing the defense, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the tool involves data location randomization, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.AR (Architecture). Finally, the paper involves implementing the tool on SGX, which could also place it under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
